#compdef tinysearch
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# tinysearch/tinysearch src/bin/tinysearch.rs `#[derive(FromArgs,
# Clone)] struct Opt { ... }` (uses Google argh derive macro, NOT
# clap-derive). The 4 output modes (search/storage/crate/wasm)
# are decoded source-direct from the upstream doc-comment on the
# Opt struct: "Valid modes are: **search** - runs search engine
# on generated storage data, **storage** - generates storage data
# for posts, **crate** - creates a Rust crate with storage data,
# **wasm** - creates a crate and generates a loadable js/wasm
# script."
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# tinysearch tinysearch R157b — tiny static-website search engine
# (the binary that builds the WASM index). Sister to the heavily-
# covered static-site-generator family (hugo/eleventy/gridsome/
# zola/jekyll-build) in the corpus.

_arguments -s -S \
  '--version[show version and exit]' \
  '--release[create production-ready output without demo files]' \
  '(-m --mode)'{-m+,--mode=}'[output mode (default Wasm)]:mode:(search storage crate wasm)' \
  '(-S --search-term)'{-S+,--search-term=}'[term to search in posts (only used in search mode)]:term:' \
  '(-N --num-searches)'{-N+,--num-searches=}'[number of posts to show in search results (default 5)]:n:' \
  '(-p --path)'{-p+,--path=}'[output path for WASM module (default ./wasm_output)]:dir:_directories' \
  '--crate-path=[path for generated crate (wasm mode only; tempdir if omitted)]:dir:_directories' \
  '(-e --engine-version)'{-e+,--engine-version=}'[engine version line for the generated Cargo.toml (TOML table definition)]:toml-fragment:' \
  '1:input file (JSON posts for codegen OR storage for inference):_files'
